        <h3>Enterprise Networking Expertise</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian is a networking expert who is proficient in network communications, computer networks, data communications, Internet protocols, and wireless applications. He profoundly understands the relationships between these technologies and their communication service architectures, designs, and implementations.</p>

        <p>His experience and background give him a unique perspective on network communications. He has extensive experience with network communication routes, equipment architectures, and design, which are data communications components of the World Wide Web and Internet architecture.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has worked with a wide range of networking and communications technologies, including:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Computer networks, network architectures, network protocols, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/pstn-voip-cellular-expert/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">communication systems, communication</a> devices, packet switching, networked systems, Internet technologies, distributed systems, and data center network architecture.</li>
          <li>Communication networks, Internet Protocols, <a href="https://wayback.archive-it.org/20635/20230207072736/https://www.ietfjournal.org/tcpip-25th-anniversary/">TCP/IP Suite</a>, TCP, UDP, IP, <a href="https://standards.ieee.org/featured/ieee-802/">Ethernet, 802.3</a> Internet protocols.</li>
          <li>Network software, data link, network, transport, and application layers (L2, L3, L4, L7).</li>
          <li><a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-security-expert/">Network security</a>, load balancing, Firewalls, IPSec, VPN, and Tunneling.</li>
          <li>Network protocols, Broadband, ICMP, IGMP, ARP, ARQ, HARQ.</li>
          <li>LAN, WAN, VPN, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/routing-switching-expert/">Routing</a> Protocols, RIP, BGP, MPLS, OSPF, Multicast, DNS, and DHCP.</li>
          <li>Bandwidth throttling, Quality of Service, QoS, Priority queuing, Classification, Provisioning, Packet Switching, and Switching.</li>
          <li>Quality of Service (QoS) relates to routing, switching, and communications systems.</li>
          <li>Network Communication Architectures, Network Infrastructure.</li>
          <li>Optical Networks, Optical Transport.</li>
          <li>Router, Switch, Bridge, Gateway, Edge Device, and core networking.</li>
          <li><a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-management-expert-witness/">Network Management</a>, MIB, SNMP, Edge Router, Core Router, Gateway.</li>
          <li>Internet Technology &amp; Infrastructure, Information Technology, Client/server applications, and 3-tiered architecture.</li>
          <li>Implementing such technologies over handsets, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/mobile-wireless-expert/">mobile devices, smartphones, cellular networks, wireless</a> technologies, architectures, standards, and systems.</li>
          <li>IP communications, digital communications, and network interfaces.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Core focus area as Networking Expert</h3>

        <div class="two-col-text-img">
          <div>
            <p>The Internet is the basic technology of the Information Age; more than any other technology, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/computer-networking-expert-witness/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">networking, and communications have changed how we</a> live, putting the Internet at our fingertips.</p>

            <p>The Networking and Communications areas focus on the architecture and design of data networks, communication systems, computer networks, and Web technologies. The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet">Internet</a> is the best example of interconnected <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_network">computer networks</a> that use the Internet protocol suite (TCP/IP) to communicate between many data networks, computer networks, and devices. Packet switching, used to group data transmitted over a digital network, is an integral part of this technology.</p>

            <p>As a networking expert, Dr. Lavian focuses on the <a href="/communications-expert-witness/data-communications-expert/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">architecture and design of data networks,</a> <a href="/communications-expert-witness/data-communications-expert/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">communication</a> systems, computer networks, and Web technologies. This includes a deep understanding of the Internet and how it works and the technologies that enable communication and connectivity between different networks and devices.</p>

            <p>Dr. Lavian's practical experience with a range of networking technologies, including ITCP/IP and packet switching, is a testament to his hands-on skills. His expertise extends to designing and implementing network architectures that support various applications and environments, including LANs, WANs, and other types of networks. He also has a proven track record in configuring network devices and services, such as routers, switches, firewalls, and gateways.</p>

            <p>In addition to his technical expertise, Dr. Lavian has experience testing and evaluating networks to ensure they function correctly and meet performance and reliability requirements. This includes experience with various network testing tools and techniques, such as network performance testing, <a href="/us-10598764-radar-target-detection-and-imaging-system-for-autonomous-car/">network security</a> testing, and network interoperability testing.</p>

            <p>Dr. Lavian's unwavering focus as a networking expert is on the architecture, design, and implementation of data networks, communication systems, computer networks, and Web technologies. His comprehensive approach and expertise in these areas enable him to assist companies and organizations in designing, implementing, and maintaining networks that cater to their specific needs and requirements.</p>
          </div>
